A clearing agent, Charles Ani, who allegedly hacked into the bank account of a customer and stole N2million, was on Wednesday arraigned before a Lagos Magistrate Court sitting in Igbosere, Lagos. Ani, 37, who resides in Ikotun, is facing a four-count charge, bordering on conspiracy, fraud and stealing, preferred against him by the police. The Prosecutor, Inspector Abass Abayomi, told the court that the defendant committed the offence on July 9, 2018. Abayomi said that Ani, unlawfully hacked into the bank customerâ€™s mobile application via phone and stole the sum of N2 million. The prosecutor said that the offence committed is punishable under Sections 411,287, 325 and 387, of the criminals Law of Lagos state 2015. Ani, however, pleaded not guilty to the crime. Magistrate Mrs T.B Are, granted him bail in the sum of N500,000, with two sureties in like sum. She said the addresses of the sureties must be verified by the court. The case was adjourned till July 22, 2019 for mention.  Ex-banker faces N2million theft charge Agent docked for diverting N4.1m meant for clearing cars N3.7m fraud: Police dock bureau de change operator Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin